description:
Filters are used to restrict results for
[Instances](#/1.0/controller/V1-Controllers-Instances),
[CloudBills](#/1.0/controller/V1-Controllers-CloudBills), and
[ReservedInstances](#/1.0/controller/V1-Controllers-Instances). The logic for
combining filters is:

* Filters which share a type are OR-ed together.
* Groups of filters with different types are AND-ed.

There are some examples below to illustrate this, using these instances:

<table class="table table-bordered">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>id</th> <th>account_id</th> <th>cloud_vendor_name</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>A</td> <td>1234</td> <td>Amazon Web Services</td></tr>
    <tr><td>B</td> <td>1234</td> <td>Microsoft Azure</td></tr>
    <tr><td>C</td> <td>1235</td> <td>Google</td></tr>
    <tr><td>D</td> <td>1236</td> <td>Google</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

#### Returns instances A and C

```json
[{
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1234"
}, {
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1235"
}, {
  "type": "instance:cloud_vendor_name",
  "value": "Amazon Web Services"
}, {
  "type": "instance:cloud_vendor_name",
  "value": "Google"
}]
```

#### Returns instance D only

```json
[{
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1234"
}, {
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1236"
}, {
  "type": "instance:cloud_vendor_name",
  "value": "Google"
}]
```

#### Returns instances A, B, and D

```json
[{
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1234"
}, {
  "type": "instance:account_id",
  "value": "1235"
}]
```
